        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat: scaffold provider plugins from init",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Extends `openclaw plugins init` so the first positional argument is the plugin name and `--type` supports `tool` by default plus `provider` scaffolds.\n- Generates provider scaffolds with TypeScript source, tests, README, package metadata, `openclaw.plugin.json`, and ClawHub validation/publishing guidance.\n- Adds a CI workflow and local validation script that dry-runs provider scaffolding, builds/tests the generated plugin, and runs ClawHub package validation.\n\n## Verification\n\n```bash\npnpm test:plugins:init-provider-scaffold\n```\n\n```text\nCreated .artifacts/plugin-init-provider-scaffold/plugin-init-test\nnpm install --no-audit --fund=false\nnpm run build\nnpm test\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  1 passed (1)\nnpm run validate\nPlugin Inspector: PASS\nBreakages: 0\nWarnings: 0\nFindings: none\nGenerated provider scaffold passed ClawHub validation\n```\n\n```bash\nnode --no-maglev ./node_modules/vitest/vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.cli.config.ts plugins-authoring-command.test.ts\n```\n\n```text\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\nTests  11 passed (11)\n```\n\n```bash\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n## Review Notes\n\n- This PR intentionally contains only the `openclaw plugins init` scaffold work; GMI externalization is in a separate PR.\n",
